# Paths excluded from the coverage gate (regex over coverage-profile lines).
# Keep this list small and well-justified.

# Entry point — wiring, flag parsing, signal handling, no behaviour worth a test.
github.com/kfet/harb/cmd/harb/main.go

# Frontend static-check helper — invoked via `make lint-frontend`,
# not exercised by go test.
github.com/kfet/harb/scripts/lintfrontend/main.go

# End-to-end test package; exercised by `make e2e`, not unit tests.
^github.com/kfet/harb/e2e/

# Reeder / GReader conformance suite — embedder-driven contract tests
# whose code is mostly assertion plumbing (t.Fatal branches on JSON
# unmarshal etc). The behaviour each contract pins is exercised in the
# packages it drives; the suite itself is test-support code.
^github.com/kfet/harb/internal/reedercompat/

# Self-update: deep filesystem I/O error branches (chmod after create,
# rename atop running exe, io.Copy mid-stream, tar.Next post-header).
# Happy path + all classified errors (network, checksum, missing entry,
# bad gzip, managed paths) are covered; contriving the remaining
# kernel-level errors adds noise without informing the behaviour.
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/selfupdate/selfupdate.go

# Store Open folds logs immediately after migrateStateLog has opened/scanned
# the same files; these error returns are only reachable by a filesystem race
# between migration and folding. The direct foldLog error path is exercised.
# buildIndex's top-level ReadDir error is similarly race-only (entries/
# was just walked by migrateEntryHashes).
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/store/store.go:130\.71,132\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/store/store.go:133\.74,135\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/store/store.go:137\.39,139\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/store/store.go:152\.3,152\.13
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/store/store.go:230\.3,230\.13

# FileOPML lazy init uses double-checked locking. The second nil-check
# inside the write-locked section is the race-loser branch — only
# reachable when two goroutines call Load concurrently on a fresh
# FileOPML and one wins the upgrade. Behaviour-equivalent to the
# winner's path; not worth a deterministic-race test rig.
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/config/config.go:103\.18,105\.3

# Reader ETag helpers: opmlFingerprint degrades to an empty string on
# OPML.Marshal failure, which is a defensive return for an encoding bug
# that doesn't happen in practice (Marshal only manipulates strings and
# already-validated structs). etagOPML / etagOPMLState then return ""
# so the handler skips ETag handling and serves a normal 200 — i.e. the
# fallback is a correctness no-op, not a behaviour to assert. applyETag
# has the same degrade-to-no-op branch on empty etag.
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/reader/reader.go:975\.16,979\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/reader/reader.go:988\.14,990\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/reader/reader.go:1000\.14,1002\.3
github.com/kfet/harb/internal/reader/reader.go:1012\.16,1014\.3
